        -: 1821:// Converts a wide string to a narrow string in UTF-8 encoding.
        -: 1822:// The wide string is assumed to have the following encoding:
        -: 1823://   UTF-16 if sizeof(wchar_t) == 2 (on Windows, Cygwin)
        -: 1824://   UTF-32 if sizeof(wchar_t) == 4 (on Linux)
        -: 1825:// Parameter str points to a null-terminated wide string.
        -: 1826:// Parameter num_chars may additionally limit the number
        -: 1827:// of wchar_t characters processed. -1 is used when the entire string
        -: 1828:// should be processed.
        -: 1829:// If the string contains code points that are not valid Unicode code points
        -: 1830:// (i.e. outside of Unicode range U+0 to U+10FFFF) they will be output
        -: 1831:// as '(Invalid Unicode 0xXXXXXXXX)'. If the string is in UTF16 encoding
